profile_data.summary:
As a data analyst with over 6 years of experience in the FinTech and E-commerce industries, I specialize in turning complex data into actionable insights. My expertise spans data cleaning, manipulation, analysis, and visualization, using advanced tools like SQL (Sybase, PostgreSQL, Amazon Redshift), Python, Jupyter Notebook, Excel, Tableau, Power BI, and QuickSight.

I have successfully contributed to multi-year, multi-phased projects, leveraging both Agile and Waterfall methodologies. My strong foundation in machine learning, statistical analysis, and database management is complemented by my subject matter expertise in back-office fixed income trade settlements.

In addition, I have hands-on experience with big data technologies like Apache Spark for large-scale data processing, AWS S3 for cloud storage, and Airflow for workflow automation. I hold a Master of Science in Data Science from the University at Buffalo, a diploma in Banking and Finance Management, and a Bachelor's in Electronics.

projects.description: In this project, I conducted a comprehensive Time Series Analysis to explore the trends and shifts in the order execution quality among the selected market centers based on the calculated net price improvement over several years. The analysis specifically looked into how each market center's performance evolved and identified significant changes in leadership in terms of execution quality, particularly noting a substantial shift in performance from multiple market centers for over 5 years. This detailed examination included the comparison of weighted-mean and weighted-median net price improvement, providing insights into the consistency and fairness of trade executions by these centers. The project's results are crucial for various stakeholders including traders, investors, brokerage firms, and regulators, helping them make informed decisions and optimize their strategies in the face of changing market dynamics.
projects.title: Dynamics of Execution Quality
